1 the state Medicaid program for the purpose of implementing Food is
2 Medicine programs as provided by this section.
3 B. Food is Medicine programs shall be designed to improve
4 health outcomes for Medicaid members with nutrition-related chronic
5 diseases through nutrition services and to reduce the need for
6 medical care.
7 C. Nutrition services covered under the state Medicaid program
8 may include, but are not limited to:
9 1. Case management;
10 2. Nutrition counseling;
11 3. Meals or pantry stocking;
12 4. Nutrition prescriptions; and
13 5. Grocery provisions.
14 D. Wherever feasible, the Authority and contracted entities
15 under the state Medicaid program shall prioritize the inclusion of
16 community-based organizations and local growers to support the
17 purchase of locally grown food in nutrition prescriptions.
